# Mocking and Integration Testing

Design for testability. Use interfaces for mocking. Separate unit and integration tests. Use fuzz testing for robustness.

---

## Design Around Interfaces for Mocking

**Define interfaces at the point of use.** Pass dependencies via constructors. Use small interfaces (see [Small Interfaces](../language/small-interfaces.mdc)).

```go
// ✅ Good: Interface for testability
type UserStore interface {
    GetByID(ctx context.Context, id int) (*User, error)
    Save(ctx context.Context, u *User) error
}

type UserService struct {
    store UserStore
}

func NewUserService(store UserStore) *UserService {
    return &UserService{store: store}
}

func (s *UserService) GetUser(ctx context.Context, id int) (*User, error) {
    return s.store.GetByID(ctx, id)
}

// In test: inject mock
type mockUserStore struct {
    users map[int]*User
}
func (m *mockUserStore) GetByID(ctx context.Context, id int) (*User, error) {
    return m.users[id], nil
}
func (m *mockUserStore) Save(ctx context.Context, u *User) error {
    m.users[u.ID] = u
    return nil
}
```

