## Use Build Tags for Integration Tests

**Separate integration tests with build tags.** Run with `go test -tags=integration`.

```go
// integration_test.go
//go:build integration

package mypkg

import "testing"

func TestIntegrationWithDB(t *testing.T) {
    db := connectToRealDB(t)  // Requires real DB
    defer db.Close()
    // ...
}
```

```bash
# Run unit tests only (default)
go test ./...

# Run integration tests
go test -tags=integration ./...
```

---

## Use Flags for Integration Test Configuration

**Use `flag` or env vars for integration test addresses and credentials.** Don't hardcode.

```go
// ✅ Good: Configurable integration test
var (
    dbAddr = flag.String("db-addr", "localhost:5432", "DB address for integration tests")
)

func TestIntegration(t *testing.T) {
    if testing.Short() {
        t.Skip("skipping integration test in short mode")
    }
    conn := connect(*dbAddr)
    // ...
}
```

```bash
go test -tags=integration -db-addr=staging-db:5432 ./...
```

